OL,4,Ccritically ill children blocked by
OL,5,CLabour
OL,7,FIt would have given parents the right
OL,8,Fto statutory paid leave and job
OL,9,Fprotection from day one for parents
OL,10,Fwhose child is diagnosed with a
OL,11,Fcritical or terminal illness, up to
OL,12,Fthe age of 16.
OL,14,FThe campaigners had been hopeful that
OL,15,Fthe Employment Rights Bill could be
OL,16,Famended by the lords after positive
OL,17,Fmeetings with government officials -
OL,18,Fbut to their disappointment, Labour
OL,19,Fordered its peers to vote against the
OL,20,Fproposal.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
