OL,7,FCeri added: "We have again reached out
OL,8,Fto ministers in the Department for
OL,9,FBusiness and Trade and to the deputy
OL,10,Fprime minister, whose bill this
OL,11,Famendment was part of, requesting a
OL,12,Fmeeting and open dialogue. To date, we
OL,13,Fhave had no response.
OL,15,F"The fight for Hugh's Law continues.
OL,16,FThis is no longer a niche policy
OL,17,Fconcern. It is becoming a matter of
OL,18,Fpublic conscience. Families deserve
OL,19,Furgent action and Hugh's Law must be
OL,20,Faddressed with the seriousness and
OL,21,Fspeed this crisis demands."
