OL,7,FA government spokesperson said: "We
OL,8,Frecognise the challenges that parents
OL,9,Fface when caring for seriously ill
OL,10,Fchildren, and we know many employers
OL,11,Fwill show compassion and understanding
OL,12,Fin these circumstances.
OL,14,F"We pay tribute to the tireless
OL,15,Fcampaigning from It's Never You in
OL,16,Fmemory of their son, Hugh. We will
OL,17,Fcontinue to work with them as part of
OL,18,Four review of carer's leave, which
OL,19,Fwill look at further support for
OL,20,Fparents of seriously ill children."
